<br>
(sorry, had to do it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )<br>
<br>
I still heartily disagree that it was the Big, Evil Beast that everyone is making it out to be. Sure, it wasn't perfect (but neither is FFA.) Sure, waiting for a schedule to come around every couple of months to take a shot at a mob can suck, but, in general, is the situation really different now? Sure, a few guilds can have free run of the large targets/planes, but what about those that can't play when a target's &quot;usual&quot; spawn window is? What if my guild wanted to take a shot at Trak, Sev, Gore, VS, etc., and their spawn windows had been pushed to around noon (US Time, when we're all at work)?<br>
<br>
&quot;I believe we were allowed a shot at inny or cazic about once every 2 months. Completely ridiculuous. &quot;<br>
<br>
Let's see... let's take that statement and modify it for a FFA situation:<br>
<br>
&quot;I believe we only got a shot at inny or cazic about once every 2 months. Completely ridiculuous. &quot; (because they were killed before we even were able to log on)<br>
<br>
The argument goes both ways, and there is no 'perfect' system. FFA has serious flaws, and so does a schedule. <p>Buadyen Adurant'linnod<br>
<b>Warder</b> of Tunare<br>
Allied Giants<br>
